The paper proposes a new evaluation protocol for cross-media retrieval, which is a task that involves both image and text processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper provides benchmarking results on several datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
